#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/consul.md:188
msgid "Canonical API name: `ptool.consul.Connection:request`."
msgstr "Canonical API name: `ptool.consul.Connection:request`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/consul.md:190
msgid "`conn:request(options)` sends a raw HTTP request through the current Consul connection defaults and returns the same `Response` object shape as `ptool.http.request(...)`."
msgstr "`conn:request(options)` sends a raw HTTP request through the current Consul connection defaults and returns the same `Response` object shape as `ptool.http.request(...)`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/consul.md:194
msgid "`options` supports the same request fields as `ptool.http.request(options)`, plus:"
msgstr "`options` supports the same request fields as `ptool.http.request(options)`, plus:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/consul.md:197
msgid "`path` (string, optional): A Consul-relative path such as `\"/v1/status/leader\"`."
msgstr "`path` (string, optional): A Consul-relative path such as `\"/v1/status/leader\"`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.10.0/lua-api/consul.md:199
msgid "`url` (string, optional): An explicit absolute URL."
msgstr "`url` (string, optional): An explicit absolute URL."

